<H3> <TI>   Dysentery Outbreak in Yaroslavl Oblast </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WE0085G Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 12 Nov 93 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 94WE0085G </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by Mikhail Ovcharov: ``Tutayev Sour Cream Found to </F>
Harbor Dystentery''] 
  [Text] A dysentery outbreak has been documented in 
Yaroslavl Oblast. One hundred fifty-five persons have fallen ill 
in the city of Tutayev, including 120 preschool children, while 
in neighboring Rybinsk 75 of the city's inhabitants are sick. It 
was discovered that all of them ate sour cream from the Tutayev 
Dairy. This dairy was closed for general cleaning and 
disinfection at the direction of the oblast state center for 
sanitary-epidemiological oversight. Production of cultured milk 
products has been temporarily banned. 


</TEXT>

