<H3> <TI>   Diptheria Cases in Ukraine </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WE0023A Moscow KOMMERSANT-DAILY in Russian No 75, 23 Apr 
93 p 14 </F>

<F P=103> 94WE0023A </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KOMMERSANT-DAILY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article; boldface as published] </F>
  [Text] An outbreak of diptheria has been established 
in Ukraine. As of today, 521 cases of the disease have been 
noted. In the opinion of epidemiologists, the current growth in 
the number of patients is directly linked to the unjustifiable 
sensation over diptheria vaccine that occurred several years 
ago. Because parents refused to have their children vaccinated, 
the rising generation's immunity against a number of diseases, 
including diptheria, is extremely low. 


</TEXT>

