<H3> <TI>   Suspected Anthrax Patients Hospitalized </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0811195393 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1706 GMT 8 Nov 93 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0811195393 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Thirty-three patients, suspected of contracting 
malignant anthrax, have been hospitalized in Almaty. 
  Deputy Chief of Kazakhstan's Sanitary and Epidemiological 
Station Rufina Ivanova told INTERFAX that the final diagnosis 
would be announced after the results of the tests were 
available, presumably on November 9. 
  The condition of three patients is rather serious and of the 
rest of the patients - satisfactory. 
  The epidemic is believed to have been caused by cattle which 
had not undergone veterinary control. 
  This year, 22 cases of malignant anthrax have been 
registered 
in Kazakhstan (last year - 25). 

</TEXT>

