<H3> <TI>   Health Ministry Announces Measures To Prevent Cholera </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0909140193 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1305 GMT 9 Sep 93 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0909140193 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Following item transmitted via KYODO] </F>
  [Text] Kyrgyzstan's Extraordinary Epidemiological 
Commission has taken urgent measures to prevent the spreading of 
cholera. The Kyrgyz Ministry of Public Health informed Interfax 
that the threat of an epidemic is coming from neighboring 
Uzbekistan, Tajikistan and Kazakhstan. 
  According to the same source, the republic's sanitary 
services will exercise sanitary control over the railways and 
motor transport. 
  Commercial charter flights to Pakistan, India, Turkey and 
Iran have been canceled until October 1. Private vendors have 
been forbidden to sell drinks, ice-cream and food stuffs. 
Control has been toughened over the quality of drinking water 
and over the rivers, lakes, and canals. 
  The Kyrgyz sanitary and epidemiological service reports that 
no cholera cases have been registered in Kyrgyzstan so far. 

</TEXT>

