<F P=101> UKRAINE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Outbreak of Typhoid Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2208142793 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1300 GMT 22 Aug 93 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2208142793 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Following item transmitted via KYODO] </F>
  [Text] One person has died and dozens of others were taken 
to hospital at famous Svalyava spa in Carpatho-Ukraine in what 
is seen as the first outbreak of typhoid there since WW II. 
Local medical experts say the disease was caused by poor 
sanitation and utilities which lack a centralized water supply 
and sewage system. 
  Members of an emergency medical commission said that 
sanitation requirements were not observed in the construction of 
many of the public lavatories and as a result, the water supply 
system was contaminated by sewage. The situation is being made 
worse because of a large number of holiday-makers from Ukraine 
and other CIS states. 
  However, Ukrainian health officials told Interfax the 
epidemic was contained and that large medical teams were sent to 
the place and measures were being taken to remove the causes 
leading to the outbreak of typhoid. 

</TEXT>

