<H3> <TI>   Gllogovc Jaundice Epidemic Blamed on Serb Authorities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1001151494 Tirana ATA in English 1306 GMT 10 Jan 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1001151494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, January 10 (ATA) -- RILINDJA Reports 40 
children and 10 grown ups affected with jaundice in two weeks' 
time in Gllogovc of Kosova. Widespread of jaundice epidemics is 
due to lack of vaccination and closing of many heath centers in 
villages, according to RILINDJA issue of January 9. 
  Epidemiologists say that water pipes of Gllogovc might have 
caused the epidemic because the water system of Gllogovc is 
still dirty since Serbian officials of the commune did not deem 
it necessary to clean the reservoir and put chlorine to water. 
Gllogovc is a commune with 100 percent Albanian population. 

