<H3> <TI>   Southern Cone Health Report Through 2 December </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0212224693 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>
<F P=103> PY0212224693 </F>
<F P=104>  -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>



<TEXT>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on epidemics and diseases monitored by Paraguay Bureau 
from 26 November to 2 December. 
<H5>  Brazil </H5>
  On 30 November, health authorities admitted that a 
meningitis 
meningococcus epidemic has been detected in Rio de Janeiro 
State. They already are discussing with the Health Ministry the 
need to import Cuban vaccine for an immunization campaign early 
next year. Rio de Janeiro and other Baixada Fluminense 
municipalities show the highest rate of the disease. A total of 
2,209 meningitis cases were registered in the state from January 
to 24 November, 499 fatal. Of this total, 725 people had 
meningitis menincoccus and 148 died. (Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO 
BRASIL in Portuguese 1 Dec 93 p 19) 

