<H3> <TI>   Edict on Committee for Sanitary, Epidemiological Control </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2011183293 Moscow RIA in English 1414 GMT 20 Nov 93 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2011183293 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, RIA -- Russia's President Boris Yeltsin has 
signed a decree on the State Committee for Sanitary and 
Epidemiological Control of Russia, qualifying it as a central 
agency of the federal executive branch. The committee will 
establish sanitary and hygienic standards and update regulatory 
acts in terms of the population's health protection against the 
adverse impact of environment and habitat. The committee is 
also due to define priorities in research into sanitary and 
epidemiological welfare of the population. 

</TEXT>

