<H3> <TI>   Total of 128 AIDS Carriers Registered in Moscow </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1511185493 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1722 GMT 15 Nov 93 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1511185493 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In the past 6 years, 128 people infected with the 
AIDS virus have been registered in Moscow -- 15 of them have 
AIDS. According to a spokesman for the local epidemics control 
commission, from 1987 through 1993 15 AIDS victims died; 4 of 
them committed suicide. 
  The average age of those infected is 28. The ratio of men to 
women among them is 8:1. 
  Two people with the AIDS virus were revealed among blood 
donors. 

</TEXT>

