<F P=102>  OW3008211793 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1620 GMT 30 Aug 93 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW3008211793 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Following item transmitted via KYODO] </F>
  [Text] "A cholera epidemic is spreading in south 
Kazakhstan, several new cases have been reported within the last 
few days," Vladimir Stepanov, Director of the Kazakh Anti-Plague 
Institute, told Interfax. He did not say how many cases had 
been registered but reliable sources say there are 18 of them. 
No deaths have been reported. 
  Stepanov said that the steps that had been taken failed to 
curb the epidemics. 
  Three cases of plague have also been registered in 
Kazakhstan 
this summer. A little girl died in the Aktyubinsk Region. The 
other two patients, a woman in the Kzyl-Orda Region and a man in 
the Atyrau region, are out of danger. 

