<F P=102> BK1101154894 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1101154894 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] India today dismissed as motivated Pakistan's threat 
of a nuclear war in South Asia if the Kashmir issue is not 
resolved peacefully. Responding to queries from newsmen on 
Pakistan foreign minister's statement in Uzbekistan, an External 
Affairs Ministry spokesman said in New Delhi that Islamabad has 
only one-point agenda. Its repeated stand on Kashmir issue is 
also well-known. He said on the other hand, India's position on 
the issue is crystal clear. Responding to a question, he said 
India is always open for negotiations to resolve all the 
outstanding disputes with Pakistan. 

