<H3> <TI>   Super-Phoenix Reactor May Be Reactivated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801150794 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1400 
GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A report has come out envisaging the reactivation of 
the Super-Phoenix [fast breeder reactor] under certain 
conditions. (Andre-Claude Lacoste) of the Nuclear Safety 
Directorate says in this report -- which was submitted this 
morning to the Industry and Environment Ministry -- that from 
the point of view of safety, the reactivation of the reactor 
could be authorized given two conditions: that the work on 
combatting sodium leaks is completed successfully, and that the 
reactor should be brought into service at reduced power for a 
few months. In other words, Super-Phoenix will be reactivated. 

