<H3> <TI>   Reportage Continues Over Munitions Plant </TI></H3>
<H4>   Foreign Ministry Spokeman Comment </H4>
<F P=102> 94WP0019B Bangkok MATICHON in Thai 1 Oct 93 p 29 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 94WP0019B </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok MATICHON </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Excerpts] On 30 September, Mr. Sakthip Krairuk, 
director-general of the Information Department, Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs, said that the UN Security Council may impose an 
embargo on Libya. [passage omitted] 
  Mr. Sakthip said that besides this, the government has taken 
steps to have the Labor Skills Development Department issue 
stipulations prohibiting Thai workers from engaging in 
activities abroad having to do with the production, stockpiling, 
and use of chemical weapons. 
  "The Thai government supports the attempt by the people of 
the world to limit the spread of chemical weapons. On 13 March, 
the government implemented a royal decree on controlling 
shipments out of the country in order to prevent the shipment of 
chemicals and implements that could be used to produce chemical 
weapons," said Mr. Sakthip. [passage omitted] 

