<H3> <TI>   EC, EBRD Agree on Nuclear Safety Account </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1211165393 Brussels EUROPE ENERGY in English 29 Oct 93 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1211165393 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels EUROPE ENERGY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Nuclear Safety: EC Agreement With </F>
EBRD on Multilateral Fund for East Europe"; as released by 
Brussels Euroscope EIS Database] 
  [Text] European Commissioners approved proposals for an 
Agreement with the European Bank for Reconstruction and 
Development (EBRD) concerning the European Community's 
contribution to the multilateral Nuclear Safety Account, when 
they met on October 20. The EC has committed itself to 
contributing 20 million Ecus to the Nuclear Safety Account, 
which is managed by the EBRD and which aims to improve nuclear 
safety in the countries of Central and Eastern Europe, including 
the former Soviet Union. The draft Council decision is scheduled 
to appear on the agenda of the Council of Ministers and the 
European Parliament in December. 

</TEXT>

